Class StringSetting

    Direct Known Subclasses:
    StringPreference

    public class StringSetting
extends AbstractSetting<java.lang.String>
    A StringSetting represents optional feature in the code. Normally this should be encapsulated as a singleton constant field so we can locate them by reflection and generate on-line documentation. Each StringSetting object defines a name for the feature a default setting and descriptive documentation. Some legacy features may be generated dynamically so the same feature may be constructed multiple times but StringSettings with the same name should be identical.

    StringSettings can be turned on and off using configuration parameters e.g. service.feature.feature-name=true The results are also cached in the AppContext as the same StringSetting may be queried a large number of times in the same request.
